<br>
Here are the latest findings from ShazLabs (TM)<br>
<br>
I did two ten minute trials to see how many T rods I could conjure using the mana robe and how many by self-rodding.  I started each trial by chaincasting rods and then burning my hp down to 100hp or less...followed by medding and then burning down more hp when able.  Self-rodding I was able to conjure 15 rods (18 actually but I had to use 3).  Using the mana robe I was able to conjure 14.<br>
<br>
It appears self-rodding has a slight advantage over the mana robe.  Self rodding will get more efficient as my spec conjuration is currently 167 and rising.  Throw in spell casting mastery later and it gets even better.<br>
<br>
I was also assisted in both trials by the Flowing Thought 1 of the Wand of Musing and the 10 percent mana savings from the Obulus Shroud.  Without those items it might have been more of a tie.  I only had standard mage buffs (TPP, Shield of the Magi) on for the experiment.<br>
<br>
I conclude Mana Robes are very useful for a pre-T rod mage, but a very expensive fashion statement for those who can conjure T rods. <p>Shazar Oom <BR>
Arch Mage <BR>
