<br>
However, any <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mage</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of sufficient level to cast the spell has at least 50% <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Specialization: Conjuration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which reduces the casting cost by 10 mana, yielding 0.300 mana per hitpoint.  With either 200% <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Specialization: Conjuration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or 50% <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Specialization: Conjuration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spell Casting Mastery 2</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> reduces the casting cost by 10% or 40 mana, and so yields 0.333 mana per hit point.  With 200% <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Specialization: Conjuration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spell Casting Mastery 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mana Preservation III</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the cost to summon a rod is reduced by 10% + 15% + 10% = 35% or 140 mana, yielding 0.444 mana per hit point, but this represents only a small fraction of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magi</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Thus as a middle ground I will assume 0.333 mana per HP, or <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3 HP = 1 Mana</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
Other casters, since they do not pay the casting cost for the rods, gain 660 mana for 900 HP, or 0.733 ~= 0.75 HP per mana, or 4 HP ~= 3 Mana.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1562<br> <font color=#333333>(6/24/02 11:13:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Rods and Self-Bandaging</span><hr size=1> Given that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> allows a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to convert HP to mana at a three to one ratio, one is tempted to consider bandaging as a means of generating mana.  To simplify matters, let us assume that the bandages are already summoned earlier, so that we can ignore their mana cost.<br>
<br>
From <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showMessage?topicID=136.topic">2nd Basic Skill: Regeneration or First Aid?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, we find the following:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bind Wounds</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> yields 1 HP per 4 skill with one bandage in 10 seconds.<br>
From <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Skills/Skills.htm">Magician Skills</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, the skill cap for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is 100, or 25 HP per bandage, or 2.5 HP per second x 6 seconds per tick = <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 15 HP per tick</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
At 3 HP = 1 mana, that is the equivalent of 5 mana per tick, or nearly as good as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Clarity</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
However, one is not sitting while bandaging.  Sitting or meditating yields between 20 and 25 mana per tick, so bandaging means losing 15-20 mana per tick over meditation.  Unless you are low on health and in danger of being killed or gaining aggro, bandaging is a bad idea.<br>
<br>
To make this perfectly clear, suppose you have 1500 HP and 3000 MP and start 50% at both.  You also have some form of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Phantasmal Armor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, any of the 50+ ones will yield 5 HP/tick regeneration.  You click one charge of a rod, taking 300 damage and gaining 220 mana.  You are now at 30% health and 57% mana.<br>
<br>
To restore 300 HP through bandaging and regeneration at 15 + 5 + 1 = 21 ~= 20 HP/tick = 15 ticks.<br>
At the end of those 15 ticks, you have 50% health.  How much mana do you have?<br>
1 mana / tick standing, without <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> TPP</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, = +15 mana ~= 58% mana.<br>
With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> TPP</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, you regain 4 Mana/tick standing, or +60 ~= 59% mana.<br>
<br>
What if you had sat down for those 15 ticks instead?<br>
<br>
With any post-50 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Phantasmal Armor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and no AA skills, sitting regen is about 10 HP/tick.<br>
In 15 ticks you regain 150 HP sitting or be at 40% health.<br>
<br>
Sitting meditating without <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> TPP</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> yields 20-25 mana/tick, call it 20/tick.<br>
In 15 ticks you would regain 300 mana or be at 67% mana.<br>
With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> TPP</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that would be another 45 mana or be at 69% mana.<br>
<br>
Which would <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>you</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> rather be?  50% health and 59% mana with bandaging, or 40% health and 68% mana by sitting?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1563<br> <font color=#333333>(6/24/02 11:17:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  What about Improved First Aid?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Improved First Aid for Magicians</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Basic AA Skill</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Alternate_Advancement_Skills/First_Aid.htm">First Aid</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> does not improve the HP regained per bandage, but simply raises the HP cap to which you can bind wounds by 10% per level, or up to 80% with three levels, instead of 50% normally.  Thus the figures from previous post still apply and sitting is still better than binding wounds, unless your life is danger.<br>
<br>
However, there are some circumstances where it might pay off.  The preceding argument assumes that sitting is an option.  If one cannot sit, and one is not casting spells, and one is below one's bind wounds threshhold, you might as well bandage.  Also, it is sometimes dangerous to go below 40% health, as one might get aggro.  As in the above scenario, with 1500 HP and 3000 Mana and 50% at both, one charge of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> will bring you to 30% health, which then gets you aggro.  With one level of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> First Aid</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, one could keep themselves at 60% health, and then taking a charge would keep you at at least 40% health.<br>
<br>
This is an unlikely scenario.  You would have to have sitting aggro, health aggro, no healer available, and nothing better to do standing before this made sense.  Casting appropriate right-click items would be vastly preferable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Improved First Aid for Others?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The main problem with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bind Wounds</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is that the mage must give up sitting in order to bind, sacrificing 20-25 mana per tick.  However, if someone else binds wounds while the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> sits and meditates, you have a winning combination for reducing down time.<br>
<br>
A melee with 200 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bind Wounds</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> skill gives 50 HP / bandage or 30 HP/tick, or 10 ticks to recover from one charge of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  In ten ticks sitting, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> gains 10 HP sitting + 30 HP bandaging = 400 HP or +27% health.  Manawise, he gains about 20 mana/tick sitting or 200 mana, plus 220 for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> = 440 mana or +15% mana.  In this case, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> First Aid</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for a melee makes sense, for themselves, and for the mage.<br>
<br>
Half a stack of bandages costs less than 10 mana, and can be essentially ignored, except for the time spent summoning.<br>
<br>
I hope this brief exposition illuminates the role of bandaging with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Master ArchMage Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
