eed a CH.  It's silly to assume that everyone will be in group CH groups so that means each heal sucks out 300 more mana or 2 CHs per rod.  If 8 people use 3 rods each, that leaves enough mana (29-3*8 or 5 rods) for 2 clerics to CH all 8 people and have enough left over to CH themselves.  So essentially 5 mages and 3 clerics at max AA mana savings have been turned into giving 8 people 1980 mana per minute for a FT of 198 per person using them or a FT of 99 for the whole group of 16 people.  Now it's not very realistic that you can put together 5 mages like this because most servers only have 1 or 2 at most mages with the gear and AA that will let you do this and even if you had 5 they would never show up all at once, but it's an interesting theoretical calculation. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90022>Xoran</a href>
<br>
Magi, 60, Xev
