<br>
1.) I've found THE most efficient way to drop rods is to go into third person mode...zoom WAAAYY out and drop at will.  You may have to rotate your &quot;camera&quot; angle till you find the &quot;sweet&quot; spot that allows you to zoom far enough away.  I never have the drop confirmation box on cause it just bugs the crud outta me, but either way would be fine using this technique.  I have yet to open a trade window or even almost open one when using this technique.  The best thing about this is you're not limited to facing a wall, so you can stand right in front of your sitting clerics and strafe drop as many rods as need be w/out ever opening a trade window with any one of them.<br>
<br>
2.)  I don't know if this has been mentioned, but the biggest reason I don't like my health to get under 50% for big fights isn't just primary agro, but also rampage.  If you get under 40% for any rampaging mobs...there's a good chance you'll gain some rampage aggro, and most of the fights where this happens...one round of rampage damage on a mage with under 40% health = dead mage = no rods for anybody. <p><p align=center>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61037>Master Tomlyn Drayke-Arch Mage</a>
</br>Gigg em'Aggs-Lvl 46 Cleric
